{
  "stem": "719.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she put some dry goods, I don't know what it was-- some, some flour-- not flour, some, I don't know, like oats, and stuff, some food that I could bring home, because she had-- they were quite wealthy.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had their own-- they grew their own stuff, and they had a lot of food, more than in big cities, because this was, like, farmers.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They usually had more.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had fresh flowers and stuff.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she gave me a whole bunch of provision to take with me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'm on this wagon-- it's like a carriage, but it's big and very bulky-- with strangers, which I don't know who they are, and well, they disappeared, but she paid that guy, that guy that was carrying us back.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we drove and drove.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We finally reached, almost, at the border of the town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My first sight was a burned-down synagogue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I walked in, and here, I'm alone, and I see the town is half burned.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So where are my parents, what am I going to do?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I'm continuing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said to this guy, in Polish-- and it was probably because he wasn't Jewish, he just got paid to take us-- to get me to this street where this big building is.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he let me off there, and I'm walking up the stairs, and I found my parents.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were alive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They didn't know how to find me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't know how to get me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the biggest welcome I could ever get.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when this guy returned back to my aunt, when we drove back, he let them know that I found my parents.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was our first holiday, the first holiday during Second World War.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
